'''Arecibo Catena''' ('''Arecibo Vallis''' until March 2013) is a catena on [[Mercury (planet)|Mercury]]. It is located at latitude 27.5 S, longitude 28.4 W, in the hilly and chaotic terrain antipodal to [[Caloris Basin]]. It is named after [[Arecibo Observatory]].

Arecibo Vallis is connected to [[Petrarch crater]].
