{{Taxobox | image = | image_caption = | domain = [[Bacteria]] | phylum = [[Planctomycetes]] | classis = [[Planctomycetacia]] | subclassis = | ordo = [[Planctomycetales]] | subordo = | familia = [[Planctomycetaceae]] | genus = '''''Rubinisphaera''''' | genus_authority = Scheuner et al. 2015<ref name=Rubinisphaera>{{cite journal |last1=Parte |first1=A.C. |title=Rubinisphaera |journal=www.bacterio.net |url=http://www.bacterio.net/rubinisphaera.html}}</ref> | type_species = ''Rubinisphaera brasiliensis''<ref name=Rubinisphaera/> | subdivision_ranks = [[Species]] | subdivision = ''[[Rubinisphaera brasiliensis|R. brasiliensis]]''<ref name=Rubinisphaera/> | synonyms = }}
'''''Rubinisphaera''''' is a genus of bacteria from the family of [[Planctomycetaceae]] with one known species (''[[Rubinisphaera brasiliensisa]]'').<ref name=Rubinisphaera/><ref>{{cite journal |title=Rubinisphaera |journal=www.uniprot.org |url=https://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/1649490 |language=en}}</ref> ''Rubinisphaera brasiliensis'' has been isolated from water from the [[Lagoa Vermelha]] from [[Brazil]].<ref>{{cite journal |title=Details: DSM-5305 |journal=www.dsmz.de |url=https://www.dsmz.de/catalogues/details/culture/DSM-5305.html |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Scheuner |first1=C |last2=Tindall |first2=BJ |last3=Lu |first3=M |last4=Nolan |first4=M |last5=Lapidus |first5=A |last6=Cheng |first6=JF |last7=Goodwin |first7=L |last8=Pitluck |first8=S |last9=Huntemann |first9=M |last10=Liolios |first10=K |last11=Pagani |first11=I |last12=Mavromatis |first12=K |last13=Ivanova |first13=N |last14=Pati |first14=A |last15=Chen |first15=A |last16=Palaniappan |first16=K |last17=Jeffries |first17=CD |last18=Hauser |first18=L |last19=Land |first19=M |last20=Mwirichia |first20=R |last21=Rohde |first21=M |last22=Abt |first22=B |last23=Detter |first23=JC |last24=Woyke |first24=T |last25=Eisen |first25=JA |last26=Markowitz |first26=V |last27=Hugenholtz |first27=P |last28=Göker |first28=M |last29=Kyrpides |first29=NC |last30=Klenk |first30=HP |title=Complete genome sequence of Planctomyces brasiliensis type strain (DSM 5305(T)), phylogenomic analysis and reclassification of Planctomycetes including the descriptions of Gimesia gen. nov., Planctopirus gen. nov. and Rubinisphaera gen. nov. and emended descriptions of the order Planctomycetales and the family Planctomycetaceae. |journal=Standards in genomic sciences |date=2014 |volume=9 |pages=10 |doi=10.1186/1944-3277-9-10 |pmid=25780503}}</ref>
